{\n "nbformat": 4,\n "nbformat_minor": 5,\n "metadata": {\n  "kernelspec": {\n   "display_name": "Python 3",\n   "language": "python",\n   "name": "python3"\n  },\n  "language_info": {\n   "name": "python",\n   "version": "3.10.0"\n  }\n },\n "cells": [\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "a1b2c3d4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "# Utonia PCA Color-Segmented Point Cloud — Segment Exporter\n",\n    "\n",\n    "This notebook:\n",\n    "1. Reads a **color-segmented point cloud** produced by the Utonia / PCA pipeline (`.ply` with per-point RGB).\n",\n    "2. Groups points by their (quantised) RGB color → one group = one segment.\n",\n    "3. Saves each segment as an individual `.ply` file.\n",\n    "4. Prints the **height** (Z-extent) and **width** (X-extent) of every segmented object.\n",\n    "\n",\n    "**Requirements**\n",\n    "````\n",\n    "pip install open3d numpy pandas\n",\n    "````"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "b1c2d3e4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 0 — Imports & setup"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "c1d2e3f4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "from __future__ import annotations\n",\n    "\n",\n    "import sys\n",\n    "from pathlib import Path\n",\n    "\n",\n    "import numpy as np\n",\n    "import pandas as pd\n",\n    "\n",\n    "try:\n",\n    "    import open3d as o3d\n",\n    "    print(f\"open3d {o3d.__version__}  ✓\")\n",\n    "except ImportError:\n",\n    "    sys.exit(\n",\n    "        \"open3d is not installed.  Run:  pip install open3d\"\n",\n    "    )"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "d1e2f3a4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 1 — Configuration\n",\n    "\n",\n    "Set `INPUT_PLY` to the path of the Utonia / PCA color-segmented point cloud.\n",\n    "Segments are distinguished by their **unique RGB color** assigned during PCA segmentation."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "e1f2a3b4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "# ── USER CONFIGURATION ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "\n",\n    "INPUT_PLY: str = \"segmented_scene.ply\"  # <-- path to Utonia PCA output\n",\n    "OUTPUT_DIR: str = \"segments_out\"        # directory where per-segment .ply files are written\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Color quantisation tolerance (0–255 scale).\n",\n    "# Points whose RGB values differ by less than this threshold are treated as the\n",\n    "# same segment.  0 = exact match, 2–5 = tolerant (handles float rounding).\n",\n    "COLOR_TOLERANCE: int = 2\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Minimum number of points for a segment to be considered valid\n",\n    "MIN_POINTS_PER_SEGMENT: int = 5\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "f1a2b3c4",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 2 — Load the color-segmented point cloud"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "a2b3c4d5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "input_path = Path(INPUT_PLY)\n",\n    "assert input_path.exists(), f\"File not found: {input_path.resolve()}\"\n",\n    "\n",\n    "pcd = o3d.io.read_point_cloud(str(input_path))\n",\n    "\n",\n    "xyz    = np.asarray(pcd.points)           # (N, 3)  float64\n",\n    "colors = np.asarray(pcd.colors)           # (N, 3)  float64  in [0, 1]\n",\n    "\n",\n    "assert len(xyz) > 0, \"Point cloud is empty!\"\n",\n    "assert pcd.has_colors(), (\n",\n    "    \"The point cloud has no color information.  \"\n",\n    "    \"Please supply the Utonia / PCA color-segmented output.\"\n",\n    ")\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f\"Loaded  : {input_path.name}\")\n",\n    "print(f\"Points  : {len(xyz):,}\")\n",\n    "print(f\"XYZ range  X=[{xyz[:,0].min():.3f}, {xyz[:,0].max():.3f}]  \",\n",\n    "      f\"Y=[{xyz[:,1].min():.3f}, {xyz[:,1].max():.3f}]  \",\n    "      f\"Z=[{xyz[:,2].min():.3f}, {xyz[:,2].max():.3f}]\")"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "b2c3d4e5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 3 — Group points by segment color\n",\n    "\n",\n    "Utonia assigns a unique flat RGB color to every PCA segment.  \n",\n    "We quantise the float colors to 8-bit integers and group by (R, G, B) tuple."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "c2d3e4f5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "# Convert float [0,1] → uint8 [0,255] and apply quantisation\n",\n    "colors_u8 = (colors * 255.0).round().astype(np.uint8)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "if COLOR_TOLERANCE > 0:\n",\n    "    # Bucket each channel into bins of size COLOR_TOLERANCE\n",\n    "    colors_quantised = (colors_u8 // COLOR_TOLERANCE) * COLOR_TOLERANCE\n",\n    "else:\n",\n    "    colors_quantised = colors_u8\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Build a structured array for fast groupby\n",\n    "color_keys = [\n",\n    "    (int(r), int(g), int(b))\n",\n    "    for r, g, b in colors_quantised\n",\n    "]\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Group point indices by color key\n",\n    "from collections import defaultdict\n",\n    "groups: dict[tuple, list[int]] = defaultdict(list)\n",\n    "for idx, key in enumerate(color_keys):\n",\n    "    groups[key].append(idx)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# Filter out tiny noise groups\n",\n    "segments = {\n",\n    "    color: np.array(indices)\n",\n    "    for color, indices in groups.items()\n",\n    "    if len(indices) >= MIN_POINTS_PER_SEGMENT\n",\n    "}\n",\n    "\n",\n    "n_total   = len(groups)\n",\n    "n_valid   = len(segments)\n",\n    "n_dropped = n_total - n_valid\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f\"Unique color groups  : {n_total}\")\n",\n    "print(f\"Valid segments (≥{MIN_POINTS_PER_SEGMENT} pts): {n_valid}\")\n",\n    "print(f\"Dropped (too small)  : {n_dropped}\")"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "d2e3f4a5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 4 — Save each segment as a `.ply` file"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "e2f3a4b5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "output_dir = Path(OUTPUT_DIR)\n",\n    "output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "saved_paths: list[Path] = []\n",\n    "\n",\n    "for seg_id, (color_key, indices) in enumerate(segments.items()):\n",\n    "    seg_xyz    = xyz[indices]\n",\n    "    seg_colors = colors[indices]          # float [0,1] for open3d\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    seg_pcd = o3d.geometry.PointCloud()\n",\n    "    seg_pcd.points = o3d.utility.Vector3dVector(seg_xyz)\n",\n    "    seg_pcd.colors = o3d.utility.Vector3dVector(seg_colors)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    r, g, b  = color_key\n",\n    "    out_file = output_dir / f\"segment_{seg_id:04d}_rgb{r:03d}-{g:03d}-{b:03d}.ply\"\n",\n    "    o3d.io.write_point_cloud(str(out_file), seg_pcd)\n",\n    "    saved_paths.append(out_file)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "print(f\"\nSaved {len(saved_paths)} segment .ply file(s) to  '{output_dir.resolve()}'\")"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "f2a3b4c5",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 5 — Print height and width of each segmented object\n",\n    "\n",\n    "| term | definition |\n",\n    "|------|------------|\n",\n    "| **height** | Z-axis extent: `z_max − z_min` |\n",\n    "| **width**  | X-axis extent: `x_max − x_min` |\n",\n    "| **depth**  | Y-axis extent: `y_max − y_min` (reported for completeness) |"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "a3b4c5d6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "rows = []\n",\n    "\n",\n    "for seg_id, (color_key, indices) in enumerate(segments.items()):\n",\n    "    seg_xyz = xyz[indices]\n",\n    "    r, g, b = color_key\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    x_min, x_max = seg_xyz[:, 0].min(), seg_xyz[:, 0].max()\n",\n    "    y_min, y_max = seg_xyz[:, 1].min(), seg_xyz[:, 1].max()\n",\n    "    z_min, z_max = seg_xyz[:, 2].min(), seg_xyz[:, 2].max()\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    width  = x_max - x_min   # X-extent\n",\n    "    depth  = y_max - y_min   # Y-extent\n",\n    "    height = z_max - z_min   # Z-extent\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    centroid = seg_xyz.mean(axis=0)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "    rows.append({\n",\n    "        \"seg_id\"      : seg_id,\n",\n    "        \"color_rgb\"   : f\"({r:3d},{g:3d},{b:3d})\",\n",\n    "        \"n_points\"    : len(indices),\n",\n    "        \"width_x\"     : round(width,  4),\n",\n    "        \"depth_y\"     : round(depth,  4),\n",\n    "        \"height_z\"    : round(height, 4),\n",\n    "        \"centroid_x\"  : round(float(centroid[0]), 4),\n",\n    "        \"centroid_y\"  : round(float(centroid[1]), 4),\n",\n    "        \"centroid_z\"  : round(float(centroid[2]), 4),\n",\n    "        \"saved_file\"  : saved_paths[seg_id].name,\n",\n    "    })\n",\n    "\n",\n    "df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── pretty console summary ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",\n    "print(\"\n\" + \"═\" * 72)\n",\n    "print(f\"  SEGMENT DIMENSIONS  ({len(df)} object(s))\")\n",\n    "print(\"═\" * 72)\n",\n    "print(f\"{'ID':>4}  {'Color':>14}  {'Pts':>7}  {'Width(X)':>9}  {'Depth(Y)':>9}  {'Height(Z)':>10}\")\n",\n    "print(\"─\" * 72)\n",\n    "for _, row in df.iterrows():\n",\n    "    print(\n",\n    "        f\"{int(row.seg_id):>4}  \"\n",\n    "        f\"{row.color_rgb:>14}  \"\n",\n    "        f\"{int(row.n_points):>7,}  \"\n",\n    "        f\"{row.width_x:>9.4f}  \"\n",\n    "        f\"{row.depth_y:>9.4f}  \"\n",\n    "        f\"{row.height_z:>10.4f}\"\n",\n    "    )\n",\n    "print(\"═\" * 72)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# ── display as a DataFrame for interactive exploration ────────────────────────\n",\n    "df"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "b3c4d5e6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 6 — (Optional) Quick statistics"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "c3d4e5f6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "print(\"Summary statistics for segment dimensions:\n\")\n",\n    "print(df[[\"width_x\", \"depth_y\", \"height_z\", \"n_points\"]].describe().round(4).to_string())"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "d3e4f5a6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## 7 — (Optional) Visualise all segments together with Open3D"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "e3f4a5b6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "# Uncomment to launch the Open3D viewer (requires a display / GPU)\n",\n    "\n",\n    "# geometries = []\n",\n    "# for seg_id, (color_key, indices) in enumerate(segments.items()):\n",\n    "#     seg_pcd = o3d.geometry.PointCloud()\n",\n    "#     seg_pcd.points = o3d.utility.Vector3dVector(xyz[indices])\n",\n    "#     seg_pcd.colors = o3d.utility.Vector3dVector(colors[indices])\n",\n    "#     geometries.append(seg_pcd)\n",\n    "#\n",\n    "# o3d.visualization.draw_geometries(\n",\n    "#     geometries,\n",\n    "#     window_name=\"Utonia PCA Segments\",\n",\n    "#     width=1280, height=720,\n",\n    "# )"\n   ]\n  }\n ]\n}